<h2 id="setting-up-project-level-logging-with-singleton-pattern">Setting
Up Project-Level Logging with Singleton Pattern</h2>
<h3 id="steps-1">Steps</h3>
<ol type="1">
<li><strong>Create a Logger Utility Module</strong></li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>Make a separate Python file (e.g., <code>logger.py</code>) to
configure logging for the entire project.</li>
</ul>
<ol start="2" type="1">
<li><strong>Implement Singleton Pattern for Logger</strong></li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>Ensure only one logger instance exists using a class with a static
method.</li>
</ul>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb2"><pre
class="sourceCode python"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb2-1"><a href="#cb2-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="im">import</span> logging</span>
<span id="cb2-2"><a href="#cb2-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb2-3"><a href="#cb2-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="kw">class</span> LoggerSingleton:</span>
<span id="cb2-4"><a href="#cb2-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>   _logger <span class="op">=</span> <span class="va">None</span></span>
<span id="cb2-5"><a href="#cb2-5" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb2-6"><a href="#cb2-6" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>   <span class="at">@staticmethod</span></span>
<span id="cb2-7"><a href="#cb2-7" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>   <span class="kw">def</span> get_logger():</span>
<span id="cb2-8"><a href="#cb2-8" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        <span class="cf">if</span> LoggerSingleton._logger <span class="kw">is</span> <span class="va">None</span>:</span>
<span id="cb2-9"><a href="#cb2-9" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>              LoggerSingleton._logger <span class="op">=</span> logging.getLogger(<span class="st">&quot;project_logger&quot;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb2-10"><a href="#cb2-10" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>              LoggerSingleton._logger.setLevel(logging.DEBUG)</span>
<span id="cb2-11"><a href="#cb2-11" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>              handler <span class="op">=</span> logging.StreamHandler()</span>
<span id="cb2-12"><a href="#cb2-12" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>              formatter <span class="op">=</span> logging.Formatter(<span class="st">&#39;</span><span class="sc">%(asctime)s</span><span class="st"> - </span><span class="sc">%(levelname)s</span><span class="st"> - </span><span class="sc">%(message)s</span><span class="st">&#39;</span>)</span>
<span id="cb2-13"><a href="#cb2-13" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>              handler.setFormatter(formatter)</span>
<span id="cb2-14"><a href="#cb2-14" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>              LoggerSingleton._logger.addHandler(handler)</span>
<span id="cb2-15"><a href="#cb2-15" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>        <span class="cf">return</span> LoggerSingleton._logger</span></code></pre></div>
<p><strong>Use the Singleton Logger in Your Code</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Import and use the logger from anywhere in your project.</li>
</ul>
<div class="sourceCode" id="cb3"><pre
class="sourceCode python"><code class="sourceCode python"><span id="cb3-1"><a href="#cb3-1" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="im">from</span> logger <span class="im">import</span> LoggerSingleton</span>
<span id="cb3-2"><a href="#cb3-2" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb3-3"><a href="#cb3-3" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>logger <span class="op">=</span> LoggerSingleton.get_logger()</span>
<span id="cb3-4"><a href="#cb3-4" aria-hidden="true" tabindex="-1"></a>logger.info(<span class="st">&quot;This is a project-level log message.&quot;</span>)</span></code></pre></div>
